posts.subject: Every day, I become more and more convinced we will kill them all ....
posts.body:
The buttsniffers. Those citizens who just can't mind their own business or stop making rules for other people. The once common mindset of "it's a free country - leave them alone" does appear almost gone.

But consider this. Those remaining are the hard core Americans. The ones that resisted both the right and the left all these years. And many want the old America back so bad they WILL kill you. With a smile.

It embarrasses such people when they realize what a festering cesspool they've left for descendants by failing to end the troublemakers early. Before they've had a lifetime to screw over the public.

Most politicians, ALL SJW, and woke journalists fit this description.

Once we start. It will feel so good it will be difficult to stop. Some of us will die. So what? It will be worth it. So many normal productive people will have great memories of us. Just watching you scream as we end your worthless lives might supply sufficient satisfaction.

Satisfying lives = killing abrasive, obnoxious people - then burying them where they never will be found. Zero closure.

posts.subject: Sure you are ready?
posts.body:
It will be real. And it won't stop for a long time. As resources for peaceful/amicable ethnic cleansing dwindle, the binary choice becomes more real.

There's no hope for participants. The survivors would be doing it for their children.

posts.subject: Attacks on infrastructure
posts.body:
Just a bad idea. Remember your rage at BLM road blocking protesters? What were you capable of at that moment? Would any have left alive?

Would YOU have any trouble running over a faggot  that you knew had destroyed the power grid?

The dumbest thing a participant can do is to mobilize fence sitters. Instead, always attack leadership. Never the lifeboat or those in it.

posts.subject: Blonde joke
posts.body:
An old, blind Marine wanders into an all-girl biker bar by mistake.

He finds his way to a bar stool and orders a shot of Jack Daniels.

After sitting there for a while, he yells to the bartender, 'Hey, you wanna hear a blonde joke?'

The bar immediately falls absolutely silent.

In a very deep, husky voice, the woman next to him says,

'Before you tell that joke I think it is only fair, given that you are blind, that you should know five things:

1. The bartender is a blonde girl with a baseball bat.

2. The bouncer is a blonde girl.

3. I'm a 6-foot tall, 175-pound blonde woman with a black belt in karate.

4. The woman sitting next to me is blonde and a professional weight lifter.

5. The lady to your right is blonde and a professional wrestler.

Now, think about it seriously, do you still wanna tell that blonde joke?'

The blind Marine thinks for a second, shakes his head and mutters, 'No...not if I'm gonna have to explain it five times.'

Counterpoint:

>Terminals and warehouses who would rather pay $5 million for a railhead and eliminate all linehaul trucking and load boards for their core local staff, who will actually show up and not flake due to things they don't have control over (vaccine and mask mandates).
>The Ports themselves, who have had vaccine mandates for several months now, want an excuse to automate. Because trains are required for the automated dock equipment, this means eliminating most drayage drivers as trailers would be loaded onto trains and sent to regional terminals instead for daycabs to pickup.
>The State government itself, who wants to encourage rail development in general because it reduces emissions and highway congestion. This includes Republicans who are all investors in the railroads.
>The DOT itself, who through changes in Carrier Authority -related policies can encourage local intrastate trucking over interstate trucking. California has considered this as is Washington becuase it would make railroads more money, and reduce emissions.

Now this does allow railroaders to make the same stunt and strike against the mandate (a threat large enough to spawn the entire modern trucking industry), but they aren't doing that because all of them got the vax. Why would the government, the ports, and the companies themselves negotiate with interstate truckers when they can build around them? This is increasingly what they are doing. It won't kill interstate trucking but it will remove all the easy drop 'n hook work.
